.:: Puzzle 3x4-Level-7-13::.
There are 4 different favourite beverages: water, lemonade, coffee, juice
There are 4 different nationalities: british, chinese, dutch, mexican
The people use 4 different means of transport: car, scooter, quad-bike, taxi
 1. the british is somewhere to the left of the person driving the scooter##5
 2. the person drinking water is on the right of the person drinking juice##1
 3. the person driving the taxi is on the far left or far right##3
 4. the person driving the quad-bike is between the chinese and the dutch##2
 5. the person driving the car is somewhere to the right of the mexican##5
 6. the person drinking juice is somewhere to the left of the person drinking lemonade##5
 7. the chinese is not the person drinking water##6
 8. the person driving the car is somewhere between the person drinking lemonade and the person drinking coffee##7
 9. the british is somewhere to the left of the dutch##5
10. the person driving the taxi is on the left of the person driving the car##1
11. the british is between the dutch and the chinese##2

.:: Answer ::.
|               |    1     |     2      |     3      |    4     |
| Beverage      | coffee | juice     | water      | lemonade     |
| Nationality   | mexican  | chinese   | british   | dutch |
| Transport     | taxi     | car | quad-bike | scooter   |

